parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a frontal collision
airbags do not deploy at a sufficient speed
airbags do not deploy despite significant impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper airbag deployment can cause injuries or fatalities, as the airbag may not provide adequate protection or may deploy with excessive force.
The absence of an airbag on/off switch can be a concern for certain individuals, such as those with medical conditions or those who require special accommodations.
symptoms: concern about airbag deployment in certain situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jump into reverse gear, leading to accidents or loss of control.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift into gear, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
The intermittent failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to fail state safety inspections, leading to potential safety risks and increased stopping distances.
symptoms: the vehicle cannot pass a state safety inspection
the brake system warning light illuminates on the dashboard.
